        {
            "abstract": "Summary: vbmp is an R package for Gaussian Process classification of data over multiple classes. It features multinomial probit regression with Gaussian Process priors and estimates class posterior probabilities employing fast variational approximations to the full posterior. This software also incorporates feature weighting by means of Automatic Relevance Determination. Being equipped with only one main function and reasonable default values for optional parameters, vbmp combines flexibility with ease of usage as is demonstrated on a breast cancer microarray study. Â© The Author 2007. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved.",
